Changing Jesus' appearance
After six days Jesus took Peter, James, and John, his brother, and led them up to a high mountain by themselves.
There before them he was transfigured. His face shone like the sun, and his clothes became as white as light.
At that moment, Moses and Elijah appeared before them. Moses and Elijah were speaking with Jesus.
Peter said to Jesus, "Lord, it is good for us to be here; if you wish, I will make three booths here, one for you, one for Moses, and one for Elijah."
While Peter was still speaking, a bright cloud enveloped them. And a voice from the cloud said, "This is my beloved Son, with whom I am well pleased. Listen to him!"
When the disciples heard this, they were troubled and fell face to the ground.
But Jesus came and touched them. He said, "Get up. Do not be afraid."
When they lifted up their eyes, they saw no one but Jesus.
They came down from the mountain. And as they were coming down, Jesus commanded them, "Tell no one about what you have seen, until the Son of Man has risen from the dead."
The disciples asked him, "Why then do the scribes say that Elijah must come first?"
Jesus replied, "So it is written." Elijah is to come first and restore all things.
